Reading material: For non-zero real numbers $a$ and $b$, if the value of the fraction $\frac{(x-a)(x-b)}{x}$ with respect to $x$ is zero, then the solutions are $x_{1}=a$ and $x_{2}=b$. Also, because $\frac{(x-a)(x-b)}{x}=\frac{{x}^{2}-(a+b)x+ab}{x}=x+\frac{ab}{x}-\left(a+b\right)$, the solutions to the equation $x+\frac{ab}{x}=a+b$ with respect to $x$ are $x_{1}=a$ and $x_{2}=b$.  
$(1)$ Understanding and application: The solutions to the equation $\frac{{x}^{2}+2}{x}=5+\frac{2}{5}$ are: $x_{1}=$______, $x_{2}=$______;  
